HEADWORD: Phraseology
<hw>Phra`se*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
phrase + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>phras⟦eacute⟧ologie</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Manner of expression; peculiarity of diction;
style.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Most completely national in his . . . <qex>phraseology</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collection of phrases; a phrase book.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Diction; style. See <er>Diction</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

